1
00:00:48,519 --> 00:00:50,200
You're always
Sick!

2
00:00:51,354 --> 00:00:53,555
You were sick
when you were my age?

3
00:00:55,767 --> 00:00:57,162
Evening, sir.

4
00:00:58,425 --> 00:01:01,263
Evening, Victor.
I didn't realize that you're still here.

5
00:01:02,925 --> 00:01:06,788
I'm just keeping James company, sir.
If that's all right...

6
00:01:08,224 --> 00:01:09,990
Very kind of you.

7
00:01:11,514 --> 00:01:14,642
- Are you better, son?
- Still cold, father.

8
00:01:14,726 --> 00:01:17,055
It's just a mild fever.
You'll be all right in the morning.

9
00:01:17,290 --> 00:01:21,198
- You always say that.
- And you always pull through, don't you?

10
00:01:22,324 --> 00:01:25,188
Now... take your medicine.

11
00:01:26,324 --> 00:01:28,043
<i>Elizabeth!</i>

12
00:01:28,323 --> 00:01:29,724
<i>Elizabeth!</i>

13
00:01:29,804 --> 00:01:31,603
Your father's drunk again.

14
00:01:31,683 --> 00:01:33,403
You should help him home, Victor.

15
00:01:33,483 --> 00:01:35,964
It's not my name he's calling, sir.

16
00:01:37,324 --> 00:01:39,484
- Father!
- Stay where you are, James!

17
00:01:39,764 --> 00:01:41,325
Father!

18
00:01:44,846 --> 00:01:46,405
<i>I told you never to come back here!</i>

19
00:02:13,968 --> 00:02:15,729
James...

20
00:02:15,889 --> 00:02:17,329
There are things you
don't understand.

21
00:02:17,409 --> 00:02:18,490
- Don't...
- I need him them to know!

22
00:02:18,609 --> 00:02:19,129
Please no!

23
00:02:19,249 --> 00:02:20,248
- No...more...lies!

24
00:02:20,368 --> 00:02:21,129
James...

25
00:02:39,211 --> 00:02:40,811
James!

26
00:02:45,812 --> 00:02:48,932
He...he wasn't your father...

27
00:02:56,613 --> 00:02:57,373
...son.

28
00:03:06,174 --> 00:03:08,014
What are you?

29
00:03:22,217 --> 00:03:24,936
- I didn't mean it! I didn't--
- Yes, you did!

30
00:03:26,376 --> 00:03:29,896
He deserved it!
And you gave it to him.

31
00:03:32,057 --> 00:03:35,377
We're brothers, Jimmy.
You realize that?

32
00:03:35,457 --> 00:03:37,458
Brothers protect each other.

33
00:03:38,058 --> 00:03:39,498
You have to be hard now.

34
00:03:39,578 --> 00:03:42,458
Hard enough they can't ever touch us.

35
00:03:42,698 --> 00:03:44,178
I want to go home.

36
00:03:44,258 --> 00:03:47,458
We can't. We stick together
no matter what

37
00:03:47,779 --> 00:03:50,459
and take care of anyone
who gets in our way.

38
00:03:50,780 --> 00:03:53,179
Can you do that, little brother?

39
00:03:57,180 --> 00:04:01,180
They're coming.
Can you run? Okay.

40
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:06,501
Keep on running.
Don't look back.

41
00:05:07,547 --> 00:05:08,628
Back-to-back!

42
00:06:06,554 --> 00:06:08,834
Enough! Enough!

43
00:06:23,115 --> 00:06:24,596
Stand down, soldier!

44
00:06:38,518 --> 00:06:40,477
Stand down!

45
00:06:43,678 --> 00:06:44,999
Victor, no!

46
00:07:09,820 --> 00:07:10,581
Ready!

47
00:07:12,221 --> 00:07:12,982
Aim!

48
00:07:13,382 --> 00:07:15,021
Wake me when it's over.

49
00:07:20,782 --> 00:07:21,863
Fire!

50
00:07:33,304 --> 00:07:35,504
My name is Major William Stryker.

51
00:07:35,584 --> 00:07:38,784
You were sentenced to death
for decapitating a senior officer.

52
00:07:38,905 --> 00:07:40,504
Is that correct?

53
00:07:40,584 --> 00:07:42,745
Apparently we have some
issues with authority.

54
00:07:42,905 --> 00:07:43,944
Just keep a lid on it.

55
00:07:44,785 --> 00:07:45,705
Sir.

56
00:07:46,505 --> 00:07:48,626
The warden tells me that your sentence
was carried out

57
00:07:48,706 --> 00:07:50,826
by a firing squad at 1000 hours

58
00:07:51,106 --> 00:07:53,907
- How'd that go?
- It tickled.

59
00:07:58,066 --> 00:08:00,347
You boys tired of running?

60
00:08:00,427 --> 00:08:03,107
Tired of denying your...true nature?

61
00:08:03,187 --> 00:08:05,428
- What do you care?
- Oh, I care...

62
00:08:06,307 --> 00:08:08,148
I care cause I know
how special you are,

63
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:10,228
how valuable.

64
00:08:14,268 --> 00:08:15,068
Look.

65
00:08:15,548 --> 00:08:18,868
You can stay here, locked up
like freaks of nature,

66
00:08:19,469 --> 00:08:21,549
or you can join me.

67
00:08:21,869 --> 00:08:26,590
I'm putting together a special team
with special privileges.

68
00:08:26,990 --> 00:08:31,390
Now tell me. How would you like
to really serve your country?

69
00:08:44,712 --> 00:08:47,111
I love this weapon more than anything
in the whole wide world.

70
00:08:47,191 --> 00:08:48,432
- You wanna know why?
- No.

71
00:08:49,592 --> 00:08:51,273
It's memorable.

72
00:08:51,473 --> 00:08:53,832
Sure, it's a little bulky,
to have to get 'em on a plane.

73
00:08:53,953 --> 00:08:56,834
You whip out a couple of swords
at your ex-girlfriend's wedding,

74
00:08:56,914 --> 00:08:59,393
they will never, ever forget it.

75
00:08:59,473 --> 00:09:03,234
That's funny, Wade.
I didn't think you liked girls.

76
00:09:04,633 --> 00:09:07,594
Right, it is...it's probably not
as intimidating as having a gun or

77
00:09:08,114 --> 00:09:11,435
bone claws or the fingernails
of a bag lady...

78
00:09:19,675 --> 00:09:23,436
- Manicure?
- Victor...easy.

79
00:09:24,156 --> 00:09:26,757
Speaking of sharp,
Fred got a new tattoo.

80
00:09:26,837 --> 00:09:30,717
- I'm concerned.
- Oh geez, Fred, you just met her last night.

81
00:09:31,037 --> 00:09:33,676
- I love her.
- You love her after one night?

82
00:09:33,756 --> 00:09:36,357
She's a gymnast.

83
00:09:36,597 --> 00:09:38,757
Bradley, take her down.

84
00:09:44,878 --> 00:09:45,718
Are you gonna puke?

85
00:09:45,959 --> 00:09:47,439
If we were meant to fly,
we'd have grown wings.

86
00:09:47,559 --> 00:09:49,999
Oh, don't worry man. See, more people
die driving than flying.

87
00:09:50,079 --> 00:09:51,038
How about from impaling?

88
00:09:51,759 --> 00:09:55,040
Hey, be nice.
Or your approximation of nice.

89
00:09:56,639 --> 00:09:58,000
Would you like a bucket?

90
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:00,961
Gentlemen, wheels down
in Lagos in five.

91
00:10:34,724 --> 00:10:39,044
- Why are we here?
- All in good time. Zero...

92
00:11:19,329 --> 00:11:22,929
- Victor, high ground lookout.
- Having fun yet?

93
00:11:28,010 --> 00:11:30,130
- Fred...
- Tank?

94
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:33,291
- Tank.
- Yeah, I got that.

95
00:12:06,454 --> 00:12:08,055
Great!

96
00:12:08,295 --> 00:12:10,895
Stuck in an elevator with five guys
on a high protein diet.

97
00:12:11,015 --> 00:12:12,575
- Oh Wade!
- Dreams really do come true.

98
00:12:12,655 --> 00:12:14,495
Would you just shut it!
You're up next.

99
00:12:14,814 --> 00:12:16,735
Thank you, sir.
You look very nice today.

100
00:12:16,815 --> 00:12:17,655
It's the green.

101
00:12:17,735 --> 00:12:19,376
Brings out the seriousness in your eyes.

102
00:12:19,456 --> 00:12:23,016
- Oh my God, do you ever shut up, pal?
- No. Not when I'm awake.

103
00:12:23,816 --> 00:12:26,616
Bradley? Top floor, please.

104
00:12:34,137 --> 00:12:36,097
Cover the elevator!
The elevator!

105
00:12:46,258 --> 00:12:47,979
Time to go to work.

106
00:13:22,743 --> 00:13:24,262
Okay!

107
00:13:24,622 --> 00:13:26,423
People are dead!

108
00:13:28,664 --> 00:13:31,904
If you haven't that mouth on you, Wade,
you'd be the perfect soldier.

109
00:13:43,905 --> 00:13:46,786
Take the diamonds, they're yours.

110
00:13:46,946 --> 00:13:48,265
I don't want your diamonds.

111
00:13:49,546 --> 00:13:50,705
I want this.

112
00:13:51,666 --> 00:13:54,986
That? That is nothing. A souvenir.

113
00:13:55,106 --> 00:13:58,387
Where did you find it?
I want the source.

114
00:13:58,786 --> 00:14:04,268
A small village, far inland,
three days from here.

115
00:14:06,068 --> 00:14:09,668
Tell him that this rock is more valuable
to me than his life.

116
00:14:09,788 --> 00:14:10,987
Ask him where he found it.

117
00:14:24,149 --> 00:14:26,230
He says it came from the sky.

118
00:14:29,790 --> 00:14:31,670
He's telling the truth.

119
00:14:32,471 --> 00:14:35,631
- You don't know their language, Logan.
- It's a meteor fragment.

120
00:14:35,751 --> 00:14:38,392
I know what it is.
I'm asking him where he found it.

121
00:14:38,911 --> 00:14:41,231
Sir, base wants to know our location.

122
00:14:41,471 --> 00:14:42,231
Shut him down.

123
00:14:45,751 --> 00:14:50,273
Tell him everyone here will die unless
he tells me where he found the rock.

124
00:14:59,993 --> 00:15:03,353
- He said that is sacred.
- Okay, fine.

125
00:15:06,635 --> 00:15:08,354
Victor...

126
00:15:24,277 --> 00:15:25,916
Victor!

127
00:15:29,156 --> 00:15:30,637
Don't even think about it!

128
00:15:32,356 --> 00:15:33,797
We didn't sign up for this.

129
00:15:37,837 --> 00:15:40,118
Put him down.

130
00:15:51,439 --> 00:15:53,400
What are you doing?

131
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:56,720
We finally got a good thing going here.
Don't you screw this up.

132
00:15:56,840 --> 00:16:00,519
- Enough, it's enough. We've done enough.
- Who do you think you are?

133
00:16:00,879 --> 00:16:03,000
This is what we do.

134
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:05,401
Maybe you'd rather be rotting
in a hole somewhere

135
00:16:05,481 --> 00:16:07,280
till they figure out a way
to do it to us, is that it?

136
00:16:07,641 --> 00:16:08,441
Uh?

137
00:16:09,601 --> 00:16:11,122
I'm done.

138
00:16:13,362 --> 00:16:15,801
You coming?

139
00:16:21,082 --> 00:16:22,883
Jimmy!

140
00:16:27,644 --> 00:16:29,083
We can't just let you walk away!

141
00:16:38,284 --> 00:16:39,605
Jimmy!

142
00:16:41,965 --> 00:16:43,805
Jimmy!

143
00:17:30,650 --> 00:17:32,850
Why are you up so early?

144
00:17:35,011 --> 00:17:37,011
Come here.

145
00:18:13,654 --> 00:18:15,295
See you baby.

146
00:18:23,697 --> 00:18:25,775
Oh, that's nice! Yeah!

147
00:18:51,739 --> 00:18:53,340
No. Come on.

148
00:19:11,621 --> 00:19:13,381
Hey, what do you do?

149
00:19:15,822 --> 00:19:17,461
You turn off the light, you win a prize.

150
00:19:18,062 --> 00:19:20,702
- Two tries for a buck.
- Come on, I wanna do it!

151
00:19:27,824 --> 00:19:29,623
Um, that's obvious.

152
00:19:32,904 --> 00:19:35,143
That's two.

153
00:19:42,545 --> 00:19:47,385
- That's a stupid trick.
- It's not a trick, man.

154
00:19:47,745 --> 00:19:49,425
C'mon.

155
00:19:51,305 --> 00:19:52,666
Bye!

156
00:20:20,108 --> 00:20:21,829
Show's over!

157
00:20:26,469 --> 00:20:29,230
I said, show's over!

158
00:20:33,390 --> 00:20:36,591
The show is never over for us, Bradley.

159
00:20:38,310 --> 00:20:41,511
- Victor.
- Aren't you gonna invite me in?

160
00:20:43,152 --> 00:20:45,672
Yeah, come on in.

161
00:20:57,473 --> 00:20:58,833
You know, I've never said anything

162
00:20:59,794 --> 00:21:02,194
to anyone...about what happened.

163
00:21:02,874 --> 00:21:05,434
I'm living a totally different life now,
but uh...

164
00:21:05,554 --> 00:21:07,633
No need to bring up the past.

165
00:21:22,115 --> 00:21:24,275
You know,

166
00:21:24,635 --> 00:21:28,237
I always thought it would be Wade
coming knocking at my door.

167
00:21:30,917 --> 00:21:34,158
Well, Wade's gone.

168
00:21:37,917 --> 00:21:40,438
I'm not afraid of you, Victor.

169
00:21:42,397 --> 00:21:44,398
I'm not afraid to die.

170
00:21:45,639 --> 00:21:50,359
How do you know?
You've never tried it before.

171
00:22:07,161 --> 00:22:09,761
Was it the wars?

172
00:22:10,280 --> 00:22:14,202
- Which one?
- All of 'em.

173
00:22:21,323 --> 00:22:23,723
Tell me.

174
00:22:24,723 --> 00:22:27,083
It's just a scratch.

175
00:22:33,483 --> 00:22:36,404
Looks like we're gonna need
new sheets again, baby.

176
00:22:36,484 --> 00:22:38,085
Yeah...

177
00:23:01,767 --> 00:23:03,847
Who the hell is this?

178
00:23:03,967 --> 00:23:06,007
It smells like government.

179
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:12,129
My God!
Haven't aged a day!

180
00:23:12,209 --> 00:23:13,808
Clean living.

181
00:23:13,888 --> 00:23:15,608
You remember Agent Zero.

182
00:23:15,728 --> 00:23:18,129
Still shooting first and
asking questions later?

183
00:23:19,568 --> 00:23:21,849
You still chewing those cheap cigars?

184
00:23:21,929 --> 00:23:26,129
Boys, please.
I have a job for you.

185
00:23:26,249 --> 00:23:28,450
- I already have a job.
- Lumberjack.

186
00:23:28,570 --> 00:23:30,730
- Eighteen grand a year?
- Eighteen five.

187
00:23:30,809 --> 00:23:32,890
Plus I haven't had
to kill anyone in a while.

188
00:23:32,970 --> 00:23:35,010
- Start to miss it?
- Yeah, right now I am.

189
00:23:35,090 --> 00:23:37,810
Zero, back to the car.

190
00:23:40,091 --> 00:23:41,692
Attaboy.

191
00:23:48,092 --> 00:23:51,172
You know, I'm not proud about the way
things ended between us.

192
00:23:51,252 --> 00:23:53,013
Conversation's over.

193
00:23:54,412 --> 00:23:57,413
Play the little house on the prairie
with a...a school teacher.

194
00:23:58,214 --> 00:23:59,494
That's just isn't you, Logan.

195
00:23:59,973 --> 00:24:01,254
And you would know, huh?

196
00:24:02,333 --> 00:24:03,093
I would.

197
00:24:03,573 --> 00:24:04,654
What do you want, Stryker?

198
00:24:06,493 --> 00:24:08,414
Bradley was killed three days ago.

199
00:24:09,935 --> 00:24:12,454
Wade, before that.

200
00:24:12,534 --> 00:24:15,535
I believe that someone is
hunting down our whole team.

201
00:24:16,496 --> 00:24:18,095
Anyone else?

202
00:24:18,215 --> 00:24:20,775
As far as I know,
Victor is safe.

203
00:24:22,136 --> 00:24:26,496
- Whoever it is, he's had names, addresses...
- I can take care of myself.

204
00:24:28,457 --> 00:24:30,497
This is not about you, Logan.

205
00:24:34,058 --> 00:24:36,017
Country needs you.

206
00:24:36,857 --> 00:24:38,457
I am Canadian.

207
00:24:39,498 --> 00:24:42,418
I know you, Logan!
I know who you are!

208
00:25:18,462 --> 00:25:20,383
What's wrong?

209
00:25:22,183 --> 00:25:23,662
Stryker came by today.

210
00:25:25,143 --> 00:25:26,422
Don't worry, I said no.

211
00:25:26,542 --> 00:25:29,183
Why is he bothering you
after all these years?

212
00:25:29,503 --> 00:25:31,864
Because I'm the best
there is at what I do.

213
00:25:31,944 --> 00:25:33,864
And what I do best
isn't very nice.

214
00:25:33,944 --> 00:25:36,865
You're not an animal, Logan.
What you have is a gift.

215
00:25:36,985 --> 00:25:40,744
A gift? You can return a gift.

216
00:25:52,666 --> 00:25:54,387
Come on, fellas!

217
00:25:57,026 --> 00:26:01,226
- Stay in the car.
- I'm just gonna ask nicely.

218
00:26:05,187 --> 00:26:07,347
Mind lettin' us go by?

219
00:26:07,707 --> 00:26:08,948
You're in some kind of
a hurry there, pal?

220
00:26:09,388 --> 00:26:10,148
Are ya?

221
00:26:10,788 --> 00:26:14,148
- Just move your truck so we can go by...
- Trying to have a conversation there, right!

222
00:26:14,228 --> 00:26:17,109
If you start something,
you'd better be ready to finish it.

223
00:26:17,709 --> 00:26:19,108
Hey guys, take it easy!

224
00:26:24,949 --> 00:26:27,109
- Your boyfriend's got a big mouth.
- I know.

225
00:26:27,949 --> 00:26:31,950
Big temper too,
so please, let us pass.

226
00:26:36,190 --> 00:26:37,471
Thank you!

227
00:26:40,352 --> 00:26:41,711
How did you do that?

228
00:26:42,431 --> 00:26:44,591
You know, power of persuasion is a gift.

229
00:26:44,991 --> 00:26:48,071
I see...
Do you, uh, have those powers over me?

230
00:26:48,311 --> 00:26:51,352
Well, you didn't stay in the car, did you?

231
00:27:07,394 --> 00:27:09,555
Why is the moon so lonely?

232
00:27:10,634 --> 00:27:12,035
Why?

233
00:27:12,315 --> 00:27:14,555
Because she used to have a lover.

234
00:27:14,635 --> 00:27:16,874
- You tell this to the kids?
- No.

235
00:27:17,915 --> 00:27:20,916
His name was Kuekuatsheu and they lived
in the spirit world together.

236
00:27:20,996 --> 00:27:23,115
Ah, it's a true story.
Right.

237
00:27:23,756 --> 00:27:27,317
And every night,
they would wander the skies together.

238
00:27:27,956 --> 00:27:32,197
But...one of the other spirits
was jealous.

239
00:27:32,517 --> 00:27:35,677
Trickster, one of the moons from South,

240
00:27:35,757 --> 00:27:39,637
so he told Kuekuatsheu
that the moon had asked for flowers.

241
00:27:39,997 --> 00:27:43,559
He told him to come to our world
and pick up some wild roses,

242
00:27:43,839 --> 00:27:47,519
But Kuekuatsheu didn't know
that once you leave the spirit world,

243
00:27:48,318 --> 00:27:50,918
you can never go back.

244
00:27:50,998 --> 00:27:56,919
And every night, he looks up in the sky
and sees the moon and howls her name.

245
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:00,921
But...

246
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:04,960
...he can never touch her again.

247
00:28:08,320 --> 00:28:10,961
Koo-koo-Kachooka got screwed.

248
00:28:12,241 --> 00:28:14,201
Kuekuatsheu.

249
00:28:20,281 --> 00:28:23,842
Means the Wolverine.

250
00:29:20,809 --> 00:29:22,770
What you're doing, Logan?

251
00:30:15,494 --> 00:30:17,295
Kayla!

252
00:31:18,262 --> 00:31:20,782
You're not from around here, are you?

253
00:31:25,462 --> 00:31:27,183
What gave me away?

254
00:31:31,383 --> 00:31:34,583
- You got an insurance in this place?
- Insurance?

255
00:31:35,184 --> 00:31:36,903
No.

256
00:31:36,983 --> 00:31:38,624
Too bad.

257
00:31:52,786 --> 00:31:56,466
