00:58:25,884 --> 00:58:28,204
Big old ass comin' out of
the front of his shirt.

508
00:58:28,484 --> 00:58:30,964
Jesus, he's gonna have a coronary
for Christ's sake.

509
00:58:31,084 --> 00:58:33,564
Is there even a stretcher big enough
to take this guy out of here?

510
00:58:35,324 --> 00:58:37,405
It ain't him I'm worried about
getting out on a stretcher.

511
00:58:37,604 --> 00:58:38,844
You're an asshole.

512
00:58:41,966 --> 00:58:42,806
Whoop his ass!

513
00:58:42,886 --> 00:58:44,926
- Let me have it.
- If you want.

514
00:58:46,006 --> 00:58:48,166
Be careful with this.
You wanna dance with me?

515
00:58:48,486 --> 00:58:49,965
Oh. Oh, that feels good.

516
00:58:53,767 --> 00:58:55,566
Hey, guess what?

517
00:58:56,647 --> 00:58:59,047
See, he's gonna talk, man.
You got him right where you want him.

518
00:58:59,167 --> 00:59:00,608
Whose side are you on, anyway?

519
00:59:34,412 --> 00:59:36,330
Now, where is Victor?

520
01:00:05,855 --> 01:00:08,494
A little dark for sunglasses,
don't you think?

521
01:00:23,616 --> 01:00:26,337
Please don't! Please! Don't, please!

522
01:00:26,417 --> 01:00:27,976
Victor!

523
01:00:32,418 --> 01:00:34,017
Where's Victor?

524
01:00:36,418 --> 01:00:42,378
Victor's... with Stryker on...
on the island, they run it together.

525
01:00:44,619 --> 01:00:45,378
What...what?

526
01:00:45,458 --> 01:00:47,339
Victor's being with Stryker?

527
01:00:47,419 --> 01:00:48,779
Yeah.

528
01:00:49,100 --> 01:00:50,460
You didn't know that?

529
01:01:10,382 --> 01:01:12,342
All that's left now is Logan, I...

530
01:01:12,422 --> 01:01:15,382
...trust you can handle that.

531
01:01:15,822 --> 01:01:17,662
I did before, didn't I?

532
01:01:17,782 --> 01:01:19,982
Oh yes, you did that.

533
01:01:22,423 --> 01:01:26,664
Our deal...it still applies, right?

534
01:01:27,943 --> 01:01:29,023
Of course.

535
01:01:29,143 --> 01:01:31,623
Now pack him
and tag him, Captain.

536
01:01:39,465 --> 01:01:41,426
What's the island?

537
01:01:41,546 --> 01:01:46,345
It's where... Striker takes them
after Victor's caught 'em.

538
01:01:46,785 --> 01:01:49,625
Wait, wait...um, what?
Takes who?

539
01:01:50,666 --> 01:01:52,466
Mutants.

540
01:01:52,827 --> 01:01:57,387
The rumor is that Stryker's doing
experiments on them there.

541
01:01:59,548 --> 01:02:01,827
Well, you never wondered
what happened to them?

542
01:02:01,907 --> 01:02:04,107
I tried no to.

543
01:02:19,269 --> 01:02:23,829
They killed her so I'd let them
put Adamantium in me.

544
01:02:25,670 --> 01:02:28,271
They killed her for a
goddamn experiment.

545
01:02:32,350 --> 01:02:34,111
Where is it?

546
01:02:34,191 --> 01:02:36,911
Logan, Stryker kept it real secret.

547
01:02:40,711 --> 01:02:42,832
But...

548
01:02:43,432 --> 01:02:45,833
- A prisoner escaped there once.
- Who?

549
01:02:45,953 --> 01:02:46,832
His name is Remy LeBeau.

550
01:02:46,992 --> 01:02:49,112
He was a street hustler from New Orleans.

551
01:02:49,392 --> 01:02:51,433
The guards at the prison
called him Gambit

552
01:02:51,513 --> 01:02:54,473
'cause he kept taking all their
money at poker, that's all I know.

553
01:02:54,593 --> 01:02:56,954
What's Stryker up to,
what's the end game?

554
01:02:59,354 --> 01:03:03,315
He's taking their powers,
trying to combine them somehow.

555
01:03:03,674 --> 01:03:05,954
It's all I know, Logan.
It's all I know.

556
01:03:07,234 --> 01:03:10,194
If I had to come back here,
I'm gonna take your head off.

557
01:03:14,276 --> 01:03:15,755
I'm coming with you, Logan.

558
01:03:17,676 --> 01:03:20,117
- There's no redemption where I'm going.
- I ain't asking.

559
01:03:56,399 --> 01:03:57,960
There's our dude.

560
01:04:04,281 --> 01:04:05,842
That's cool.

561
01:04:06,282 --> 01:04:08,402
But I'm gonna gonna go and cover
the back if he runs.

562
01:04:08,482 --> 01:04:09,681
I'm not havin' a fight with him.

563
01:04:09,761 --> 01:04:11,241
- Yeah right.
- What?

564
01:04:11,322 --> 01:04:12,602
I am havin' fights with everybody?

565
01:04:12,721 --> 01:04:14,602
Don't dogs kill cats?

566
01:04:14,722 --> 01:04:16,602
Just go cover the back, will ya?

567
01:04:28,523 --> 01:04:31,243
Are you Remy LeBeau?

568
01:04:32,444 --> 01:04:34,004
Do I owe you money?

569
01:04:34,204 --> 01:04:35,405
No.

570
01:04:36,404 --> 01:04:38,405
Then Remy LeBeau I am.

571
01:04:56,007 --> 01:04:58,847
Large blind is 100,
and the small blind's 50.

572
01:04:59,686 --> 01:05:01,487
May I deal you in?

573
01:05:01,567 --> 01:05:03,688
Now what can I get for 17 bucks?

574
01:05:04,608 --> 01:05:06,488
17 dollars?

575
01:05:07,168 --> 01:05:09,129
A cab ride home, perhaps.

576
01:05:13,528 --> 01:05:15,809
You're my brother's new babysitter, John?

577
01:05:17,008 --> 01:05:18,689
I ain't Bradley, Victor.

578
01:05:18,769 --> 01:05:20,489
And your creepy black
coat don't scare me.

579
01:05:20,569 --> 01:05:21,970
Really?

580
01:05:22,329 --> 01:05:23,690
It worked on Dukes.

581
01:05:24,490 --> 01:05:27,651
What a shame, 'cause now I'm gonna kill you
so Logan never gets the chance.

582
01:05:28,650 --> 01:05:31,290
So what brings you to our fair city, sir?

583
01:05:31,410 --> 01:05:33,291
Victor Creed.

584
01:05:35,371 --> 01:05:36,531
And who's that?

585
01:05:37,331 --> 01:05:39,411
The man I'm gonna kill.

586
01:05:40,731 --> 01:05:43,893
He works for a man named Stryker
on, uh, on an island.

587
01:05:44,773 --> 01:05:48,052
- I just need to know where it is.
- Why would you think I know that?

588
01:05:48,332 --> 01:05:50,972
Well, 'cause I know who you are, Gambit.

589
01:05:52,012 --> 01:05:56,094
You are the guy who escaped and you are
the guy who's gonna take me back there.

590
01:05:57,893 --> 01:05:59,574
You know, John...

591
01:05:59,654 --> 01:06:01,614
There's something I always
wanted to tell you.

592
01:06:06,855 --> 01:06:09,214
You're predictable.

593
01:06:12,856 --> 01:06:15,295
I can feel your spine, Johnny Boy.

594
01:06:16,016 --> 01:06:19,016
That's funny.
I never knew you had one.

595
01:06:22,096 --> 01:06:25,736
Those are mighty nice tags
you have on there, sir.

596
01:06:26,736 --> 01:06:29,777
The men who took me
wore tags just like 'em.

597
01:06:33,138 --> 01:06:35,097
Hey, now Bob, you listen to me...

598
01:07:07,220 --> 01:07:10,982
Two years I was rottin' in that hell,
and I'm never going back.

599
01:07:13,622 --> 01:07:16,102
Oh, shiny.

600
01:07:18,182 --> 01:07:20,103
Tell me something, Jimmy.

601
01:07:20,863 --> 01:07:22,983
Do you even know how to kill me?

602
01:07:23,103 --> 01:07:25,543
I'm gonna cut your goddamn head off.

603
01:07:26,383 --> 01:07:28,264
See if that works.

604
01:07:37,545 --> 01:07:39,144
You're gettin' slow, old man.

605
01:07:48,186 --> 01:07:50,426
Son of a bitch.

606
01:07:53,827 --> 01:07:56,306
You're gonna die for
what you did to her.

607
01:08:19,549 --> 01:08:20,910
Victor!

608
01:08:30,150 --> 01:08:32,111
That's a nice stick.

609
01:09:28,757 --> 01:09:30,636
Shithead. Here's the deal.

610
01:09:30,836 --> 01:09:32,997
See, you're gonna take me to this
island, where I can kill Creed,

611
01:09:33,077 --> 01:09:35,718
Stryker, pretty much everyone
you hate in this world.

612
01:09:35,958 --> 01:09:37,557
Do you understand?

613
01:09:38,878 --> 01:09:40,198
You really want to kill 'em.

614
01:09:40,278 --> 01:09:42,558
As long as you stay
out of my way, yeah.

615
01:09:56,200 --> 01:09:57,320
Colonel.

616
01:09:58,401 --> 01:09:59,440
General?

617
01:09:59,520 --> 01:10:01,841
Is this Weapon XI?

618
01:10:03,040 --> 01:10:06,040
All their strenghts
but none of their weaknesses.

619
01:10:06,120 --> 01:10:08,081
You really hate them, don't you?

620
01:10:08,401 --> 01:10:10,162
No, I don't hate them.

621
01:10:10,282 --> 01:10:13,562
After 20 years of working with them,
I just know what they can do.

622
01:10:18,042 --> 01:10:21,883
If we win this war before it starts,
and save countless lives in the process.

623
01:10:22,003 --> 01:10:24,963
Preemptive action is
the only action here, General.

624
01:10:25,483 --> 01:10:29,443
The days of our country sitting
on the sidelines are over.

625
01:10:30,044 --> 01:10:33,445
We need to take the fight to the enemy
before they take the fight to us.

626
01:10:34,005 --> 01:10:36,764
- I admire your passion, I do.
- Thank you.

627
01:10:37,524 --> 01:10:40,204
But this is as far as it goes.

628
01:10:40,524 --> 01:10:42,645
Weapon X was a... a hickup.

629
01:10:42,725 --> 01:10:44,406
We know about your son, Bill.

630
01:10:44,526 --> 01:10:46,165
We know he's a mutant.

631
01:10:46,245 --> 01:10:49,246
And we know he killed your wife.
You shouldn't have kept that from us.

632
01:10:49,326 --> 01:10:50,767
That...

633
01:10:52,405 --> 01:10:55,246
- That has nothing to do with my work.
- Bullshit!

634
01:10:55,726 --> 01:10:58,807
You're too close to this.
I'm sure you know it.

635
01:11:01,087 --> 01:11:04,408
You're right.
I...I won't lie to you.

636
01:11:07,247 --> 01:11:12,048
My son did bring the problem home for me.

637
01:11:12,448 --> 01:11:14,928
But I took an oath...

638
01:11:15,328 --> 01:11:18,329
to protect the American people

639
01:11:18,609 --> 01:11:20,689
from every threat,

640
01:11:20,889 --> 01:11:22,570
both foreign

641
01:11:29,330 --> 01:11:30,891
...and domestic.

642
01:11:38,451 --> 01:11:40,371
- You don't like flying, huh?
- I'm fine.

643
01:11:40,491 --> 01:11:41,651
Just concentrate on
what you're doing.

644
01:11:41,771 --> 01:11:43,411
You sure? You got a bit of sweat on your brow there.

645
01:11:43,491 --> 01:11:46,452
- Very funny. Just keep your eyes on the...
- On the what? Clouds?

646
01:11:46,732 --> 01:11:49,772
We're jumpin' up and down loke a yoyo here.
Where did you get this thing anyway?

647
01:11:49,972 --> 01:11:52,293
Oh, this is my baby, I won her in a game.

648
01:11:52,373 --> 01:11:55,292
- Jacks over fives.
- Great.

649
01:11:56,453 --> 01:11:58,813
Relax. We're almost there.

650
01:12:00,374 --> 01:12:01,853
There it is.

651
01:12:01,973 --> 01:12:03,414
The island.

652
01:12:03,654 --> 01:12:07,014
Three Mile Island.
Hiding in plain sight.

653
01:12:09,935 --> 01:12:12,414
Noone's gonna sneak around
a nuclear reactor.

654
01:12:12,534 --> 01:12:14,855
They think it's gonna turn them into freaks.

655
01:12:14,935 --> 01:12:16,055
Like you?

656
01:12:16,175 --> 01:12:17,736
Right.

657
01:12:19,135 --> 01:12:20,816
All right, you ready?

658
01:12:20,896 --> 01:12:22,376
Cause it's now or never.
Let's go.

659
01:12:22,457 --> 01:12:23,697
About time.

660
01:12:32,537 --> 01:12:35,497
Hey, if it's make you feel any better,
this is really gonna hurt.

661
01:12:35,617 --> 01:12:39,018
Oh yeah. It kind of does actually.

662
01:12:39,618 --> 01:12:40,939
Good luck.

663
01:12:41,418 --> 01:12:42,979
Likewise.

664
01:12:44,698 --> 01:12:46,139
Oh shit.

665
01:12:52,779 --> 01:12:53,899
How are you doing?

666
01:12:54,420 --> 01:12:55,820
Is everything alright?

667
01:12:56,820 --> 01:12:59,140
- Is he ready yet?
- A few hours.

668
01:12:59,460 --> 01:13:01,460
Will he respond to my commands?

669
01:13:01,580 --> 01:13:03,381
Yes, Colonel.

670
01:14:03,347 --> 01:14:04,467
Logan.

671
01:14:05,747 --> 01:14:07,468
Welcome back to the war.

672
01:14:08,787 --> 01:14:11,988
Before you gut you,
I wanna know why.

673
01:14:13,149 --> 01:14:15,389
I needed your powers
for the pool.

674
01:14:15,469 --> 01:14:17,069
For the what?

675
01:14:17,149 --> 01:14:20,228
A mutant killer.
The dead pool.

676
01:14:21,029 --> 01:14:24,630
Years of searching him, to find him,
finding the right powers

677
01:14:24,750 --> 01:14:29,230
that can coexist in one body
without ripping it apart.

678
01:14:30,431 --> 01:14:33,991
My son was the first piece of the puzzle.

679
01:14:34,751 --> 01:14:36,671
Logan, you are the last.

680
01:14:37,070 --> 01:14:38,751
You made Weapon XI possible.

681
01:14:40,191 --> 01:14:40,991
I...

682
01:14:41,472 --> 01:14:46,993
I asked you to help but...
you said you wanted the quiet life.

683
01:14:47,273 --> 01:14:48,033
Well...

684
01:14:49,072 --> 01:14:54,952
I've learned that nothing motivates
the men in your family like revenge.

685
01:15:10,555 --> 01:15:12,234
Who are you?

686
01:15:12,955 --> 01:15:15,435
Oh she's a real old friend.

687
01:15:26,556 --> 01:15:28,557
Do you really think we'd
just let you walk away?

688
01:15:29,716 --> 01:15:32,117
You are a dangerous man.

689
01:15:32,317 --> 01:15:34,877
I like to keep an eye on dangerous men.

690
01:15:35,117 --> 01:15:37,198
Tell him about the
day you died.

691
01:15:42,998 --> 01:15:46,118
They gave me a shot of
hydrochloride thiazide.

692
01:15:48,119 --> 01:15:51,800
It reduces the heart rate so low,
it appears you flatline.

693
01:16:03,041 --> 01:16:05,481
Don't be angry with her.

694
01:16:05,961 --> 01:16:09,202
Real credit to your species.

695
01:16:11,762 --> 01:16:15,681
Did you know that her sister
has diamond-hard skin?

696
01:16:15,801 --> 01:16:19,122
Kayla's mutation
is tacto-hypnosis.

697
01:16:19,242 --> 01:16:22,042
She can influence people as
long as she touches them.

698
01:16:22,162 --> 01:16:24,723
Quite a useful tool in the seduction.

699
01:16:24,923 --> 01:16:27,443
It was never real, my friend.

700
01:16:32,004 --> 01:16:34,124
It was real for me.

701
01:16:35,844 --> 01:16:39,004
I told you if you came down this road,
you wouldn't like what you'd find.

702
01:16:46,125 --> 01:16:48,125
That story you told me...

703
01:16:48,246 --> 01:16:51,486
about man who gets flowers for the moon...

704
01:16:52,606 --> 01:16:55,407
I had it backwards.

705
01:16:57,367 --> 01:17:00,768
I thought you were the moon
and I was your Wolverine.

706
01:17:02,927 --> 01:17:05,968
But you were the Trickster, aren't you?

707
01:17:06,168 --> 01:17:08,608
I am just the fool that got played.

708
01:17:10,488 --> 01:17:13,888
The worst part of this is
I should have known.

709
01:17:16,329 --> 01:17:18,848
But I ignored my instincts.

710
01:17:21,649 --> 01:17:24,529
I ignored what I really am.

711
01:17:28,610 --> 01:17:31,410
Well, that will never happen again.

712
01:18:01,134 --> 01:18:03,174
- Colonel.
- Not now, Kayla.

713
01:18:03,254 --> 01:18:05,893
I have done everything you've asked.

714
01:18:07,014 --> 01:18:08,934
My sister...

715
01:18:09,455 --> 01:18:11,694
You said that if I help you,
you'd let her go.

716
01:18:12,295 --> 01:18:14,135
Kayla, it's not as simple as that.

717
01:18:14,215 --> 01:18:16,975
Her mutation is unique.
Quite beautiful.

718
01:18:17,095 --> 01:18:19,136
We just need a little more time
to analyze it, that's all.

719
01:18:19,216 --> 01:18:20,176
You let him go?

720
01:18:23,856 --> 01:18:26,176
- Victor, please.
- You can't let him go.

721
01:18:26,256 --> 01:18:28,536
- You can't beat him, Victor.
- Give me the Adamantium.

722
01:18:28,656 --> 01:18:29,737
- Tests came out...
- We had a deal!

723
01:18:29,817 --> 01:18:31,937
You would never survive the operation.

724
01:18:34,297 --> 01:18:37,258
- I can take anything he can.
- No, you can't.

725
01:18:38,378 --> 01:18:39,497
You are my favorite soldier, Victor.

726
01:18:40,217 --> 01:18:41,778
Be patient, time will come.

727
01:18:42,098 --> 01:18:43,098
He's using us!

728
01:18:51,819 --> 01:18:55,980
How about this time, you die for real?

729
01:18:56,660 --> 01:18:57,859
Let me go.

730
01:19:00,580 --> 01:19:02,940
Your mindgame don't work on me.

731
01:19:03,340 --> 01:19:04,501
Victor!

732
01:19:37,344 --> 01:19:39,265
Feels good, doesn't it?

733
01:19:40,425 --> 01:19:42,505
All that rage...

734
01:19:43,664 --> 01:19:45,185
Do it.

735
01:19:45,265 --> 01:19:46,745
Logan!

736
01:19:47,786 --> 01:19:48,865
You're not an animal.

737
01:19:49,865 --> 01:19:51,746
Oh yes, you are.

738
01:19:55,106 --> 01:19:56,267
Do it.

739
01:20:00,107 --> 01:20:02,187
Finish it.

740
01:20:25,270 --> 01:20:26,030
Logan?

741
01:20:29,670 --> 01:20:31,310
My sister.

742
01:20:31,510 --> 01:20:32,870
They have my sister.

743
01:20:33,991 --> 01:20:36,471
Please, I didn't trick you deliberately.

744
01:20:37,231 --> 01:20:38,671
It was real for me too.

745
01:20:41,911 --> 01:20:43,792
Please, I'm so sorry.

746
01:20:43,872 --> 01:20:46,273
They have my sister.

747
01:20:46,711 --> 01:20:48,232
Where is she?

748
01:20:53,232 --> 01:20:56,153
- Activate Weapon XI.
- The binding process is incomplete.

749
01:20:56,233 --> 01:20:57,114
Just do it!

750
01:20:57,194 --> 01:20:58,074
Now!

751
01:21:57,239 --> 01:21:58,880
You are okay? Come on.

752
01:22:48,625 --> 01:22:49,866
Ok...

753
01:22:50,586 --> 01:22:51,826
Perfect.

754
01:22:52,106 --> 01:22:53,946
- Kayla, get these kids out of here.
- Logan...

755
01:22:54,026 --> 01:22:55,866
Find another way out.

756
01:22:55,946 --> 01:22:57,786
Come on, let's go!

757
01:22:58,747 --> 01:23:00,666
Wade, is that you?

758
01:23:04,188 --> 01:23:07,268
I guess Stryker finally figured
out how to shut you up.

759
01:23:17,588 --> 01:23:18,349
Wade...

760
01:23:19,789 --> 01:23:21,270
You don't have to do this.

761
01:23:22,629 --> 01:23:23,829
Or maybe you do.

762
01:23:38,271 --> 01:23:39,112
Shoot on sight!

763
01:23:47,272 --> 01:23:48,792
I can help! Point me at 'em!

764
01:23:49,112 --> 01:23:49,992
Go!

